Does the salience of cultural issues differ conditional on ethnic minorities, religion, or communist legacies?

OI: The salience of cultural issues should be higher in countries that have politically significant ethnic minorities

Religion and the salience of morality issues

OI: Countries religiosity levels are positively associated with the salience of cultural issues, especially those related to morality.

There is no significant correlation between countries religiosity levels and the salience of morality issues at elections:

Note: Data on issue salience is from the Manifesto project dataset:

Lehmann, Pola, Simon Franzmann, Denise Al-Gaddooa, Tobias Burst, Christoph Ivanusch, Sven Regel, Felicia Riethmller, et al.2024. Manifesto Project Dataset. Manifesto Project. https://doi.org/10.25522/MANIFESTO.MPDS.2024A.

Data on religiosity is from the European Social Survey Wave 11 integrated file:

European Social Survey European Research Infrastructure (ESS ERIC). (2024). ESS11 integrated file, edition 2.0 [Data set]. Sikt - Norwegian Agency for Shared Services in Education and Research. https://doi.org/10.21338/ess11e02_0

Communist legacies are coded based on:

Kitschelt, Herbert, Zdenka Mansfeldova, Radoslaw Markowski, and Gabor Toka. 1999. Post-Communist Party Systems: Competition, Representation, and Inter-Party Cooperation. Cambridge Studies in Comparative Politics. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press. https://doi.org/10.1017/CBO9781139175173.

Countries with politically significant ethnic minorities are coded based on:

Rovny, Jan.2024. Ethnic Minorities, Political Competition, and Democracy: Circumstantial Liberals. Transformations in Governance. Oxford: Oxford University Press.
